	<tr><td colspan="2" bgcolor="#666699" vAlign="TOP">
	<p><font face="verdana, arial, helvetica" size="2" color="#FFFFFF">I appreciate the input I have gotten. <img src="images/smilies/biggrin.gif" border="0" alt="Big Grin"> I have been curious about this for a while now. The downside to my play-time is that "regular" groups are not really an option. I work until 5am, and log on from about 0530-0800 or so, depending on when my daughter wakes up. (0600 is not rare for her). Besides weekends, I don't have a lot of time to play at all. Then, even on weekends, I play while the family is asleep, from about midnight to about 0600 or so, max. I am in a large, good guild, but only 1-2 other people are usually on during my play time. So pick-up (ewww) groups are the only option I have, unless I want to work on tradeskills or something...<br />
<br />
I guess overall I have been too nice of a person on EQ. I try to have fun, and help friends out, which ends up costing me XP, AAs, gear, etc... I have passed up a number of good groups to help people with quests, keys, etc. And as a part of this, it never crossed my mind to take a tradeable BST item away from a BST just to sell it...  I just don't work that way. In fact, in one freaky weird WoS group I had, we ended up having 4 BST items drop (most were also Monk and Druid, but we had no Monks or Druids). The BST got all 4 of those and no one else ended up getting gear. We also had 2 runes drop, which the BST passed on because he had gotten so much gear. But he was estatic. I never once though "Hmm, we should make him choose ONE of those and roll of the others to sell..."  He even asked on the 2nd-4th ones if we were sure he could loot it. Again, I thought "Well, duh, non one else here can use it." and STILL didn't think "Hmm, I bet that sells for a lot in the Baz..." He later said something about how thankful he was, and how surprised he was that we let him loot it all, and didn't want it for friends or alts or selling or something...  And I STILL didn't think "Hmmm, I could sell that and buy myself something" but instead said "Why? If it had been 4 Cleric items I would have expected to get them all if they were upgrades..." and really didn't understand how anyone could have a problem with it... We just all thought he was really lucky... But that's the way the loot fell...</font></p>
	
	<p><p><img src="/forums/images/sig_separator.gif" width="282" height="11" Alt="Hey! Watch where you point that thing!"><br>
<font face="verdana, arial, helvetica" size="2" color="#FFFFFF">

