	<tr><td colspan="2" bgcolor="#666699" vAlign="TOP">
	<p><font face="verdana, arial, helvetica" size="2" color="#FFFFFF">In pickup groups, I find NBG to not be a common thing. Normally all in group will roll on a drop regardless of what class it's for (like cloth classes rolling on the ornate bracer mold in BoT<img src="images/smilies/rolleyes.gif" border="0" alt="Roll Eyes">). In OoW on TT, it's almost always 1 rune; 1 item; 1 quest drop. You are free to roll on anything until you have one of each, and then you wait until everyone else has something of that item until you can roll again.<br />
<br />
I was in a group recently where they were doing that rule, however since the enchanter and myself were added later to the group we were not allowed to roll on anything until the remaining two in the group that had not yet received a rune had won one. We went along with this and it sounded fair from a point of view, however it annoyed me that we weren't allowed to roll since we were contributing to the group's kills (and the enchanter actually won the first roll on a rune, but was told after she rolled we were out<img src="images/smilies/mad.gif" border="0" alt="Stirn">).</font></p>
	
	<p><p><img src="/forums/images/sig_separator.gif" width="282" height="11" Alt="Hey! Watch where you point that thing!"><br>
<font face="verdana, arial, helvetica" size="2" color="#FFFFFF">

