	<tr><td colspan="2" bgcolor="#666699" vAlign="TOP">
	<p><font face="verdana, arial, helvetica" size="2" color="#FFFFFF">IMHO:<br />
<br />
I am in a group and something drops - if it is <b>not</b>  class specific no-drop, I think everyone in group has the right to roll for it.  Once you win something, you wait until everyone has had that opportunity to roll again.  Class specific no-drop stuff goes without saying as do pieces for epics.  Class specific no-drop and epic drops have priority to the class.  <br />
<br />
NBG basically to me states "Even though I was here and put forth effort just like you, you get the upgrade because you have crappy gear".  Um, no.   There is alot of stuff that drops that I need, but I don't expect to get prioirty because I have lousy gear.  Players always have the opportunity to pass on a roll.  <br />
<br />
Like I said, all IMHO.  <br />
<br />
/cast Resist Fire<br />
<br />
edit:  Example removed - apparently it was difficult to understand.</font></p>
	
