	<td bgcolor="#666699" width="100%" valign="top">
	
	<!-- Main Post Body -->
	<table width="100%" cellpadding="4" cellspacing="0" border="0">
	<td bgcolor="#4D4D73"><img src="images/posticon.gif" border="0" alt="Old Post"></td><td width="100%" bgcolor="#4D4D73"><font face="verdana,arial,helvetica" size="1" color="#FFFFFF">
	Posted 12-11-2004 <font color="#FEDE01">06:14 PM</font></font></td>
	</tr>
	<tr><td colspan="2" bgcolor="#666699" vAlign="TOP">
	<p><font face="verdana, arial, helvetica" size="2" color="#FFFFFF">Problem is just about no one is going to pass on a roll.<br />
<br />
If a Stone of Perfidious Wanting dropped while I was grouping with my enc and everyone there wanted to roll for it, I'd be madder than heck.   Everyone will get something if they stay long enough, and chances are you'll get something else that you would even use.  IMO it is always better to give an item to someone who will actually use it rather than someone who will just sell it.  To me that just seems down right greedy, but to each his own.  Not to mention once that person gets an item he's out of all future rolls until they go full circle, so it's not like they're cheating anyone out of anything.  The same amount of loot will still drop, and no one will get more than one piece.<br />
<br />
I've only ever been in one situation where someone wanted to roll for an item that they couldn't use, but the rest of the group booed that person down till they decided it was much better to have the group and get a chance at more loot than it was to cause a ruckus and get a piece of loot that would probably disgruntle alot of people.<br />
<br />
It's very rare to see that on BB, but it is becoming more common with the current influx of new players.  My offtime is mostly spent playing little alts that have some touch of the former EQ to them. )<br />
<br />
PS - Not sure where the charisma note came from but it's also good for Divine Intervention.</font></p>
	
	<p></p>
	<p></p>
	</td></tr></table>
